    "20 ADVANCING WASHING TONS INTEREST fl T I HAD PROSPEROUS YEAR Annual Report Explains Pay ment of 9 Per Cent f on Stock_ By HARRY GUSACK The American Telegraph and Telephone Company during the year 1922 had one of the most prosperous years in its history according to the annual report of the company made public today Taxes paid by the Bell system Federal State and localamounted to 41215000 this being an increase of 6702900 over 1921 the report states Another interesting item is that traffic expenses of the Bell system increased 4575577 in 1922 over the previous year The volume of wages mostly telephone operators increased 31 per cent while the number of calls handled jumped 95 pei cent Stock Pays 9 Per Cent How the American Telephone and Telegraph Company can pay a 9 per cent dividend on its stock is taken up in the report This stock is widely distributed particularly in the District of Columbia where an educational campaign by the Chesapeake and Potomac Telephone Company has given it more promi nence than ever before In answer to the question as to how the A T T can pay 9 per cent when none of its"
